1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:20,000
Kitten Economics Episode 3: Inflation.

2
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Welcome back. Today we learn one core economics idea with kittens.

3
00:00:45,000 --> 00:01:15,000
In Kitty Town, fish tokens are used to buy snacks.

4
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:45,000
At first, one token buys one fish treat. Then more tokens are printed while fish supply stays limited.

5
00:01:45,000 --> 00:02:10,000
Soon, one token buys only half a treat. That is inflation: prices rise because money grows faster than goods.

6
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Recap: Inflation. Use this rule in real decisions. Comment: More Kitten Economics.
